The Biden-Harris Administration has taken quick action to support the people of East Palestine, Ohio, following a train derailment. The Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) deployed a team to assist with emergency and environmental response efforts. The Department of Transportation (DOT) is also investigating the cause of the derailment. The Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) is coordinating with local and state agencies. The administration has offered additional federal assistance if needed. The Department of Health and Human Services (HHS) and Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) are sending medical personnel and toxicologists to conduct public health testing and assessments. The goal is to evaluate individuals exposed to chemicals and ensure timely communication to the public. The administration is committed to supporting the community and holding Norfolk Southern accountable. Various federal agencies, including the EPA, NTSB, DOT, HHS, CDC, and FEMA, are playing their part in the response efforts.